INSERT INTO nodes (_index, created, edited, tag, identity, editor_id, place, timing, hits, displays, body) VALUES (1263,911038137,911038137,'madness_10a',134,134,115,140,12,5,'<font color=ccbb11>Date: Sat, 14 Nov 1998 00:00:57<br>\r\nSubject: madness/suicide, etc.<br>\r\nFrom: lel-b<br>\r\nLocation: rotterdam<p>\r\n\r\ni wrote the pieces about madness because my brother is in a hospital, i was in a hospital, my grandmother was in a hospital. that is why. that is the answer. you can hide for months, years even. but there will always be a day when it creeps back up to you without warning.</font>');
INSERT INTO nodes (_index, created, edited, tag, identity, editor_id, place, timing, hits, displays, body) VALUES (1264,911038183,911038183,'madness_10b',134,134,115,130,12,6,'<font color=ccbb11>there is always the fear that that time will bring the one fatal blow. that act of desperation that so baffles most people. one terrifying moment in which the pain is so extreme that the only answer is to destroy oneself. is this not the human condition i am speaking of?<br>\r\n\r\ncamus wasn\'t the first or last to ask the critical question, the fundamental question of philosophy: is life worth living?</font>');
INSERT INTO nodes (_index, created, edited, tag, identity, editor_id, place, timing, hits, displays, body) VALUES (1265,911038657,911038657,'afflicted',134,134,115,130,17,35,'<font color=ccbb11>Date: Fri, 13 Nov 1998 23:29:51 +0100<br>\r\nFrom: nobody <equator@king.dom.de><br>\r\nLocation: rotterdam<p>\r\n\r\nRandall Jarrell almost certainly killed himself. He did so not because he was a coward, nor out of any moral feebleness, but because he was afflicted with a depression that was so devastating that he could no longer endure the pain of it.</font>');
INSERT INTO nodes (_index, created, edited, tag, identity, editor_id, place, timing, hits, displays, body) VALUES (1266,911038821,911038821,'auster_01',134,134,115,180,15,21,'<font color=ccbb11>Date: Fri, 13 Nov 1998 23:42:45<br>\r\nSubject: paul auster \"mr bones\"<p>\r\n\r\n\r\nThe gushing, rhapsodic letter of recommendation she wrote for him in his senior year helped clinch a full scholarship for Willy at Columbia. Mrs Swanson was his muse, his protector and his good luck charm all rolled into one, and at that point in Willy\'s life, the sky was definitely the limit. But then came the schizo flip-out of 1968, the mad fandango of truth or consequences on a high-voltage tension wire.</font>');
INSERT INTO nodes (_index, created, edited, tag, identity, editor_id, place, timing, hits, displays, body) VALUES (1267,911038870,911038870,'auster_02',134,134,115,110,19,23,'<font color=ccbb11>They shut him up in a hospital, and after six months of shock treatment and psycho-pharmacological therapy, he was never quite the same again. Willy had joined the ranks of the walking wounded, and even though he continued to churn out his poems and stories, to go on writing both in sickness and in health, he rarely got around to answering Mrs Swanson\'s letters. The reasons were unimportant....</font>\r\n\r\n\r\n');
