INSERT INTO nodes (_index, created, edited, tag, identity, editor_id, place, timing, hits, displays, body) VALUES (1435,930743008,930743105,'enigmatic_voices',160,160,139,150,20,52,'<font color=ccbb11>Mail to therLands, created by chrof+m.st. at Wed, 30.Jun 1999<br>\r\nSubject: ENIGMATIC VOICES 001<br>\r\nLocation: /////<p>\r\nAgain it was night, when you tore me away from the images of my dream. You freed me from my sleep to lure me to the city limits, where the brick wall, inhabited by small animals, extends to the south like a monument, like a threat, like a promise. For you it\'s become an altar, a place of devotion, in which you confide your secrets, your tears and desires. Your ear close to the wall of irregular growth strains to hear words of consolation, promise or fortune, your ear. The echo of your expectations is supposed to reach you.');
INSERT INTO nodes (_index, created, edited, tag, identity, editor_id, place, timing, hits, displays, body) VALUES (1437,930743140,930743140,'enimgatic_voices1',160,160,139,110,15,50,'<font color=ccbb11> A firm voice, constant and well-defined, as if there was no perilous journey over the hills and over the mountains (far away). And once again it is me you have chosen as witness of these hopes, as a second to such a ridiculous deed. As if friends were only there to stand by one in failure and grief with a wounded heart. You ignored my indifference, misunderstood my tiredness, for my only desire is sleep and deep in my heart I am without a trust. You made me !');
INSERT INTO nodes (_index, created, edited, tag, identity, editor_id, place, timing, hits, displays, body) VALUES (1436,930743058,930744665,'enigmatic_voices2',160,160,139,110,19,51,'<font color=ccbb11>Your witness of inexplicable trust. As if an impossible stand-in could have saved you from the uncertainty of how far the threat reaches, how far the wall is running into the land. Maybe to the coastline and even to the bottom of the sea like a continuation of your prayers, like the carrying off of all your essential values into the distance of an unknown place. Who are you going to call from there? By which means will you make yourself heard?');
INSERT INTO nodes (_index, created, edited, tag, identity, editor_id, place, timing, hits, displays, body) VALUES (1438,930743246,930743246,'enigmatic_voices3',160,160,139,220,23,44,'<font color=ccbb11>Mail to therLands, created by chrof+m.st. at Wed, 30.Jun 1999<p>\r\nFortune might befall you in the impossible. You are deprived of your strength, you are incapable of taking the first step. It\'s a situation of alienation, seemingly forlorn and without means, but still intended: a remote-controlled life without a destination, a place promising security. You are alone and no one really knows you. You have to ask the animals, whether they know if there\'s a future and a prize? It\'s going to cost you years to make yourself understood, to study their language. Only to ask for the right to speak to them in the end and with a nervous glance, to question them about the paths of your dreams. Your impatience might arouse their distrust - and what\'s impatience but fear and impotence in your conceptionless world of shadows - they would take it as an uncalculable offence, a danger and they\'ll flee from you without listening or returning to that place. You\'d have to invent a new language, the language prior to speech. A voice without sound, words in the loo!');
INSERT INTO nodes (_index, created, edited, tag, identity, editor_id, place, timing, hits, displays, body) VALUES (1439,930743304,930743304,'enigmatic_voices4',160,160,139,70,25,32,'<font color=ccbb11>!<p>\r\nThe texture of a rule which is no rule but form and figure of the uniqueness of your intent and desire to communicate, to ask for advice in your singular situation.');
INSERT INTO nodes (_index, created, edited, tag, identity, editor_id, place, timing, hits, displays, body) VALUES (1440,930743436,931355476,'enigmatic_voices5',160,160,139,160,32,22,'<font color=ccbb11>\r\nMail to therLands, created by chrof+m.st. at Wed, 30.Jun 1999<p>\r\nNot even words or hints. Soft but still distinct marks of the urgence of your struggle to gain knowledge from <b>animals</b>: who you are and where you are going. But first and above all you have to make clear that your intentions are all peaceful. And hints are not enough for that. Almost causing a contrary effect, should the impetus of your hands and eyelids be too sharp. A kind of pressure no one of us can stand.  Making clear you are no danger is really difficult to communicate. And if I\'m not quite mistaken there is only one rare mean to guarantee the peacefulness of your appearance. Behave naturally, as if nothing were at stake.');
INSERT INTO nodes (_index, created, edited, tag, identity, editor_id, place, timing, hits, displays, body) VALUES (1441,930743471,931355497,'enigmatic_voices6',160,160,139,120,31,20,'<font color=ccbb11>\"Nothing?\" - I hear you call. \"Everything is at stake, because it\'s me.\" I understand your terror and I even share it. But it\'s you who wanted me as a witness and you wanted my advice. You have to communicate with the <b>animals</b>, show your complete lack of intentions, you have to learn to forget, what is leading you and who you are. You have to act as if e!\r\nverything is behind you. You are dead and without fear and without pain and without the urge to gain consolation and fortune.');
INSERT INTO nodes (_index, created, edited, tag, identity, editor_id, place, timing, hits, displays, body) VALUES (1442,930743559,930743559,'enigmatic_voices7',160,160,139,90,24,19,'<font color=ccbb11>Mail to therLands, created by chrof+m.st. at Wed, 30.Jun 1999\r\n<br>\r\nLocation: /////<p>\r\n\r\nBut as it is, if circumstances are not completely against you - but who\'s the one to decide, to foresee that far? You know about all those causes and side-causes, about motives and reasons, threatening to rule your plan as any plan in inexplorable ways and directions, of which only the closest are predictable and still uncertain...');
INSERT INTO nodes (_index, created, edited, tag, identity, editor_id, place, timing, hits, displays, body) VALUES (1443,930743603,930743603,'enigmatic_voices8',160,160,139,160,23,19,'<font color=ccbb11>...if so you are a little lucky and your stake is practically unlimited, you might find answers, precious hints and rare instructions, which were unthinkable and even impossible, the very moment you asked your questions, which all of a sudden line up with probabilities, become self-evident and you wonder why you hadn\'t found them on your own, without the complicated, the expensive assistance of  those now friendly animals. Because all these solutions are plain to see, no enigma left. Though this is the moment, as I think I know, of utmost danger. Caution! The rules and regulations that defeated you, the complete inspection of the promised paths is not o!');
INSERT INTO nodes (_index, created, edited, tag, identity, editor_id, place, timing, hits, displays, body) VALUES (1444,930743664,930743664,'enigmatic_voices9',160,160,139,100,24,25,'<font color=ccbb11>\r\nOnly deceitful; there\'s truth in deceit, which is more depressing and more inevitable than any illusion. So don\'t be afraid of lies as you shouldn\'t be afraid of your and other people\'s errors and failures. Because the truth of these tears means terror and means danger. Be austere in your triumph and with caution; the reason for your fear is always imminent.');
INSERT INTO nodes (_index, created, edited, tag, identity, editor_id, place, timing, hits, displays, body) VALUES (1445,930743728,930743728,'enigmatic_voices10',160,160,139,160,20,26,'<font color=ccbb11> Mail to therLands, created by chrof+m.st. at Wed, 30.Jun 1999<p>\r\nOnce the animals have spoken take their lies as truth. This is not going to give you protection on your way. But it might help to understand a little of your present and your future. And you will get tired, you\'ll be too inert to hope, your pace will slacken. You still don\'t know where the wall runs. It\'s length and it\'s width, the emptiness and the night will not become any more tolerable, but your dream is interspersed with joy und delight. I do repeat with my loudest voice: Your enigma, your grief are irrecovable and absolute.<p> \r\n-- marcus steinweg 1999');
INSERT INTO nodes (_index, created, edited, tag, identity, editor_id, place, timing, hits, displays, body) VALUES (1446,930744839,930745618,'mum_lila',160,160,139,280,56,62,'From: Lila, May 25 1999<br>\r\nLocation: Utrecht<br>\r\n<img align=left valign=texttop src=/equator/upload/agent02/mum.gif>\r\nApparently there is no fruit to bear from your intense efforts of the past--and you won\'t be able to seperate theapples from the oranges in your mixed-up life. At the same time there is a quick wild thing or two, though I\'d advise you to check and double check to make sure they\'re perfectly wanted, moral, and not hurtful. Hmmmmm?<br>\r\nOr do you think you can listen to more obscene predictions of life on the edge of fantasy? Try it out for a minute  or three, you should also sense some fabulous fleeting pulsations from musculature and secret L-factors.');
INSERT INTO nodes (_index, created, edited, tag, identity, editor_id, place, timing, hits, displays, body) VALUES (1447,931117126,931117126,'never_get',160,160,139,40,21,23,'<font color=ccbb11> Date: Fri, 2 Jul 1999 16:06:45 +0200<br>\r\nSubject: ach!<br>\r\nFrom: samy alsiteverwas (natjam@knuut.de<br>\r\nLocation: z.zt. cologne<p>\r\n\r\nach! never get through to you');
INSERT INTO nodes (_index, created, edited, tag, identity, editor_id, place, timing, hits, displays, body) VALUES (1448,931278757,931278757,'battery_point',160,160,139,180,16,13,'<font color=ccbb11>Date: Tue, 6 Jul 1999 13:28:51<br>\r\nSubject: battery point <br>\r\nFrom: chrof (steinweg@dom.de)<br>\r\nLocation: thersite<p>\r\n\r\nBattery Point Deconstructed<p> \r\n\r\nDeconstruction, in its broadest sense, challenges the certainty of rational logic, the basis of the western intellectual tradition since the Enlightenment. By implication therefore, it challenges the normative conventions that have been applied to planning and urban design, for it postulates that reason is essentially dishonest, in that there can be no absolute certainty. In particular, words and symbols used to express inward thought have no absolute meaning.');
INSERT INTO nodes (_index, created, edited, tag, identity, editor_id, place, timing, hits, displays, body) VALUES (1449,931278799,931279065,'battery_point02',160,160,139,80,22,4,'<img width=250 height=150 src=/equator/upload/agent02/photo1.jpg><p>\r\n<font color=ccbb11>...Reason is seen as a tyranny that suppresses uncertainty. Deconstruction is a quintessential post-modern perspective, but not the only one.');
